\paperw12240\paperh15840\margl1800\margr1800\margt1440\margb1440\f0\fs24\cf0
\pard\plain \fi720\sl288\slmult1\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 God\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s own envoy stepped up to the edge of a barren plateau. Far below her painted toes lay a red rock valley. This valley coursed into a desert, where its dry riverbed choked on sand. The sight of it stirred her memory, for that valley and its river once sustained an idyllic clime. The riverbanks bloomed with wildflowers. The sweet smell excited every little butterfly and bee. Chirping birds hunted those drunken insect swarms, and the meat of those birds fed foxes, and all of them, at different stages of life, from womb to carrion corpse, fed lizards. The meat of the lizards fed larger birds, and on the circle went. Now, that circle was a flat line of compacted sand which never saw rain. The only things which grew were lichens that looked like brown rags. They sustained nothing but themselves as they soaked up the evening mist.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She stepped off the cliff.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her white robes clung to her body as she fell.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The wind ripped tears from her eyes.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Better for her that she should die instead of be stuck with these memories. Better for her, but only her; for everyone else, she needed to see the day through.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She clenched her fists and swerved out of her fall with the power of flight. She zipped through the red rock valley. She followed its course out into the desert, tracing the sinuous route of the fossilizing river. On any other day, the emptiness here would have made her sick. On this day, the absence of life brought a somber peace, for if the world was alive with creatures, they would see her in this state. It was better that she was alone.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She bit her lip to keep from breaking.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Embarrassed, she wiped her cheek clean from the stain of tears. She slowed down to gather herself, and now she bit her lip in anger, because all those plants and animals were dead, elsewhere they were dying, and she\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d thought to pity herself instead of them.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Her selfishness was appalling.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Unconscionable.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What was the stain of her memory compared to the suffering of the littlest creature?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Remembering her purpose, she resumed her flight. Neither guilt nor shame would stop her from reaching the appointed place at the appointed time. She flew across the wasteland, chasing the setting sun. At length, the tip of the sun dipped below the rim of the world and she saw her destination: a wide stone square sitting alone in the middle of desert. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She picked up speed the swept down, alighting upon the stone square with a whirlwind.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Pellora was already there, sitting on a drop cloth stool. She turned her shaven head to give the envoy a minimal greeting, then returned her sight to the sweep of pink sunset.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pellora was younger. Her white robes were less carefully arranged, and fashioned as they were from a transparent silk they left nothing to the imagination, even where the material bunched. It was not seductive, and neither was it meant to be. The transparency was meant to draw attention to the falseness of the boundary, as clothes were only an artifice disguising a naked and uncomfortable truth. If Pellora could have managed it, she would turned her skin transparent as well, for in her god\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s view, all boundaries, even the body, were false.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  The envoy detested Pellora. Rival was not a strong enough a word. Neither was enemy. Evil would ascribe malice, and that wasn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t quite correct, for Pellora\u8217\'92s fault was ignorance. What but ignorance else could drive that rude smirk? And a bitter ignorance it was. Pellora was near enough to the root of all troubles.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m surprised you are alone.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh?\u8221\'94 Pellora asked. \u8220\'93You were expecting assassins? I\u8217\'92m not }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 always}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  scheming. A little prophylactic murder does give a little high, but all of this is different. We\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92re working together on this betrayal.\u8221\'94 There was an eagerness about her. There was always an eagerness about her, and by the envoy\u8217\'92s judgment, that eagerness was fake.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Keep your voice low,\u8221\'94 the envoy said.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Why?\u8221\'94 Pellora replied, chuckling. \u8220\'93They can\u8217\'92t hear us. They\u8217\'92re too far away. In fact, even if They were close, I doubt it would matter. I doubt any of the gods were ever capable of hearing. Prayers go }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 right}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  through them. You know how they always keep themselves at a distance. I always took it as a sort of divine regality, but lately I\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92ve begun to wonder.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The envoy grumbled. Pellora grimaced in turn.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, please,\u8221\'94 Pellora said. \u8220\'93Don\u8217\'92t pretend to fear them. Your god, my god, neither are in control.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I know.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I know that you know,\u8221\'94 Pellora said. \u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m only surprised that you came to me about it.\u8221\'94 She stood up and kicked her stool. Instead of clattering onto the stone, it blinked out of existence. \u8220\'93Maybe I shouldn\u8217\'92t be surprised, because you and I are so similar.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93We are nothing alike.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93On the other hand,\u8221\'94 Pellora continued, \u8220\'93Killing my god is a natural consequence of my philosophy. One might say my god demands it. Your god, however\u8230\'85I didn\u8217\'92t take you for a heretic.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Pellora, I will not countenance your foolishness. Not today.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re not a heretic? Do you have a different definition of the word \u8216\'91betrayal\u8217\'92?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My god lives only to sustain this world against the likes of you and yours.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So, what? You kill Him, and then you kill me, is that it?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You are going to use me to open the door so that you can kill me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I am not a schemer like you, }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, please. That\u8217\'92s not what\u8217\'92s happening here. You\u8217\'92ve lost faith.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t blame you. I have, too. Why would anyone struggle day after day, only to have every victory turned into  What use is a victory if the remnants of those you defeat inevitably find some foothold to nurse their strength, and, in time, start the fight all over again? You crave a battle to end all battles. I crave the same.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No,\u8221\'94 the envoy said, \u8220\'93You crave the end of all things.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How will you do it?\u8221\'94 }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Pel sensitive to it. World changign to hear the voice of woman.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How will I do }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 what}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 ?\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Fulfill our agreement.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What agreement? I want to hear you say it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How will you kill Them?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Kill who? I aim to kill lots of people.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I will not indulge your sadism.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is that where you draw the line? Killing your own god is an odd item to put below it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93So long as you kill yours, too.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes, that is inevitable isn\u8217\'92t it. Both must killed so that we can finally kill each other.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93How will you do it.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Does it matter?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Yes.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Well it took a lot of thinking. And dreaming.\u8221\'94 she said fervently. \u8220\'93I had a dream wherein I discovered the words which could contain Them. I assembled a chorus to chant Their names. It sounds silly, but if you heard Their names repeated, each note entering on the finger, each new voice swelling the chord until the wash of noise did shake the earth\u8230\'85such was the echo in the valleys that one and twenty voices blossomed into twelve and thousands!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She was speaking now to the sky, to the stars beyond it. There was a younger face beneath her wrinkling years. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It did subdue Them,\u8221\'94 she claimed. \u8220\'93For an age of peace, it stilled Their being. Then I woke back up into this nightmare\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 into the futility of Their illness. I resolved to be done with it. It was then that I realized that there is only. I\u8217\'92ve chosen to delve into the mysteries of the Black.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 what}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 !?"}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Oh, please. Don\u8217\'92t act like you didn\u8217\'92t already know the answer. You\u8217\'92ve thought of it, too. Only, you\u8217\'92re too much of a . You absolve your conscious by deferring the indignity to me. Which, I hope you know, makes you worse than me. Not only will their death be on your hands, but so will the stain of shirking responsibility. Well, I won\u8217\'92t let you off so easy. When the gods are all dead, you\u8217\'92ll have no one left to repent to but to yourself, and to }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 me}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 . I will not forgive you for it.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I didn\u8217\'92t expect you would.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You know, I\u8217\'92ve come to despise you. More than enemies. At this point, I want more than to defeat you. I want to visit you on your death bed to remind you that we all turn to dust, and that despite all your ambitions you will never live to see them through. Despite how special you think you are, all that's left for you is an eternity of loneliness at best, and an eternity of hell at worst. I want you to know that your entire life\u8217\'92s work was a waste, and the only thing you will experience for the relatively short time you have left is the of my triumph over you.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0  I say all this to make sure you understand that, after}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  the deed is done, all our conventions will be cast aside. The next time we meet, it will be death.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I found a spot of Black free floating out there in the void. I have aimed it at the mountain where They watch.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She hadn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t assentedd but the enemy had read her }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She flew up into the sky. Such was her speed, that her white robes buzzed behind her. She pushed through the thick of the sky to find the uninterrupted night. The stars, in their sparkling multitude, were always . She floated there in the liminal space between the void and the bright earth.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She drifted up against the chunk of Black. It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s enormity humbled her. She\u8217\'92d seen larger stones, but this was of a substance which defied all size comparison. It would seem larger next to objectively larger things. And though it floated freely, it was, somehow, still embedded in the void; its edges extruded out of the black space which was infinitely distant, all to make a jagged body, chaotically pinched, a spiky complex of scar contractures on the skin of night. An ugly wound from an old and ugly injury. With such a substance, size was not a relational thing, but a deep internal feeling; in size, it felt to her like a small city had been glassed into obsidian, then broken, then smushed up into a ball, then hammered into a shape which evoked despair.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The thing turned, slowly, through its tempted orbit. Its fractaled surface multiplied the points of stars. It turned, slowly, to reveal a flat, cylindrical head that would strike the world like a hammer.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 And what was the world, now?}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 From this height, she could see it all. She could remember it all.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 That once green paradise was crusted over with history. Grim monuments to abandoned civilizations trimmed every river bend\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 gray lesions on the skin of a dying world. Great pastures which once nursed untold scores of life had been ruined by herds of cattle.}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  The waters were all drunk dry. Bare mountains rumpled up the of tectonic plates, old wounds. It had been a slow, slow death. Most of the colors dipped into gray. And there amongst it was her god. Blinding white, and sparkling, H}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 e looked like a fallen star twinkling atop the tallest peak of the Goree mountains. }
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Of creation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Childhood. The birth of language and its quick evolution. The first kingship. The first sailing ship. The first minted silver coin and the first imitation of it; a thin bit of copper washed in pewter. The urge to horde. The night she gained the sight. Anatomy lessons with the flayed. The long charter of the fleshcraft guild. The temptations of priests. The origins of debt. The operations of war. The shock of famine. King Sixa\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s plan to pot the desert with wells. The explosion of Mount Volgi which poisoned half the continent. The Folzeek revolution and the splintering of the zagoqa tribes. The beginning of table manners. The deep hunger driving demons through the tunnels of the world. Greed chewing at every city\u8217\'92s roots. Salosa\u8217\'92s denuded self becoming a goddess. All these memories were condensed into one big emotion, and the tears were boiled away when the meteor set fire in the atmosphere. When it smashed through the clouds she sank into more primitive categories of feeling.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Fear of her father.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Anger at injustice.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And finally, guilt.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Each wound in her life now seemed like an accident, arbitrary, for how far could her god have seen when He was weaving her fate? He could not see this massive spot of Black coming to end Him.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Black fell upon Him.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The collision shook the earth.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The soundlessness of space muted her sigh of awe.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 for at A round shockwave spread, swept away the god cloud like it was nothing, flattened the armies battling below it, then went out to the sea to steam the surface of the waters, stir up the magnificent phytoplankton blooms, thousands of miles long, glowing prussian-blue in whirling gyres. The shock went on to circle the globe, sweeping clouds thin, dragging a shade of dust behind it.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And so the stage was set for the beginning of the end. It was her against the shadow. The gods were dead. One of them would finally win.}}